sentences: Tutu Jones (born September 9, 1966) is an American electric blues and soul blues guitarist, singer and songwriter.
Since 1994, Jones has released five albums.
He began his career in adolescence, as a drummer, graduating from backing his uncles Barefoot Miller and L. C. Clark (the latter in 1976) to working with Z. Z. Hill and R. L. Burnside.
Meanwhile, working on his own guitar playing, by 1989 Jones had moved on to fronting his own bands.
This in led to the recording of his debut album, I'm For Real, on JSP Records in 1994.
Soul followed two years later, and Staying Power in 1998.
